 and a New World metaphysics. This volume was substantially completed before Irving Goldman's death, but Peter Wilson has edited it for publication, providing a thorough introduction to Goldman's work. Stephen Hugh-Jones has contributed an afterword, setting the work in the context of contemporary Vaupés ethnography.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mrz 2022) 0aIndians of South AmericavReligion. 0aIndians of South AmericaxReligion. 0aRELIGIONvEthnic &ampxTribal. 0aReligionvEthnic and ampxTribal. 0aSOCIAL SCIENCEvAnthropologyvGeneral. 0aSocial sciencesvAnthropologyvGeneral. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / General.2bisacsh1 aHugh-Jones, Stephen.1 aWilson, Peter J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWilson, Peter, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertColumbia University Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311044247240uhttps://doi.org/10.7312/gold1302040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780231503617423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780231503617/original  a978-3-11-044247-2  Columbia University Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK